#### DESPATCHES FROM PALESTINE IN THE CENTURY BEFORE THE EXODUS.

#### No. I <span id="fr_155"></span>[1](#fn_155.md)

1\. To the king, my lord,  
2. my gods, <span id="fr_156"></span>[2](#fn_156.md) my Sun-god, <span
id="fr_157"></span>[3](#fn_157.md)  
3. by letter  
4. I speak, <span id="fr_158"></span>[4](#fn_158.md) even I
Su-arda-ka <span id="fr_159"></span>[5](#fn_159.md)  
5. thy servant, the dust of thy feet:  
6. at the feet of the king my lord,  
7. my gods, my Sun-god,  
8. seven times seven do I prostrate myself.  
9. The king of (the country of) … directed the mouth  
10. to make war:  
11. in the city of <span class="smallcaps">Kelte</span> <span
id="fr_160"></span>[6](#fn_160.md)  
12. he made war against thee the third time.  
13. A cry (for assistance) to myself  
14. was brought. My city  
15. belonging to myself  
16. *adhered to* (?) me.  
17. Ebed-tob <span id="fr_161"></span>[7](#fn_161.md) sends  
18. to the men of <span class="smallcaps">Kelte</span>;

<span id="page_63">p. 63</span>

19\. he sends 14 pieces of silver, and  
20. they marched against my rear;  
21. and the domains of the king my lord  
22. they overran. <span class="smallcaps">Kelte</span>  
23. my city Ebed-tob  
24. removed from my jurisdiction;  
25. the *pleasure park* (?) of the king my lord  
26. and the fortress of Bel-nathan <span
id="fr_162"></span>[1](#fn_162.md)  
27. and the fortress of Hamor <span id="fr_163"></span>[2](#fn_163.md)
from  
28. before him and his justice  
29. he removed. Lab-api  
30. the *halting* (?) in speech occupied  
31. the fortress of … <span class="smallcaps">Ninu</span> and  
32. now Lab-api  
33. together with Ebed-tob and  
34. \[his men\] has occupied the fortress of … <span
class="smallcaps">Ninu</span>  
35. …when the king to his servant

*Lacuna*.

<span class="smallcaps">On the Edge</span>

1\. As regards this matter, No!  
2. twice has the king returned (this) answer.

